\v 4 \w Then|strong="H3318"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* champion\f + \fr 17:4 \ft “Champion”: literally “a man of the space between.” This is usually taken to mean a champion who will fight another in a kind of proxy battle, but its precise meaning is uncertain as it only occurs here and in verse 23 in the whole of the Old Testament.\f* \w came|strong="H3318"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w of|strong="H8034"\w* \w the|strong="H3318"\w* \w Philistine|strong="H6430"\w* \w camp|strong="H4264"\w*. \w His|strong="H3318"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w Goliath|strong="H1555"\w* \w from|strong="H3318"\w* \w Gath|strong="H1661"\w*, \w and|strong="H3318"\w* \w he|strong="H3318"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w six|strong="H8337"\w* cubits \w and|strong="H3318"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w span|strong="H2239"\w* \w tall|strong="H1363"\w*.\f + \fr 17:4 \ft “Six cubits and a span tall.” This is equivalent to around nine and a half feet. The Septuagint and a manuscript from Qumran have four cubits and a span, equivalent to six and a half feet.\f*
